-- 2012-10-30T08:12:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-30/portuguese-advertising-market-may-shrink-15-this-year-omg-says.html
Advertising sales in  Portugal  are
forecast to drop 14.8 percent in 2012, according to Omnicom
Media Group.  Sales are projected to decline to 526 million euros ($678
million) from 618 million euros in 2011, OMG, a unit of  Omnicom
Group Inc. (OMC) , said in an e-mailed statement from its office in
Lisbon.  Advertising revenue from Portugalâ€™s free-to-air television
stations is expected to fall 13 percent while Internet and cable
television sales are forecast to rise five percent and six
percent, respectively, OMG said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
